<div><a href="/2014/05/14/opinion/nigeria-negotiations-shehu-sani/index.html?iid=article_sidebar">Negotiation way to #BringBackOurGirls</a></div>
<div class="cnn_stryscbx2">
updated 8:48 AM EDT, Wed May 14, 2014
</div>
<div class="cnn_stryscbx3">
<a href="/2014/05/14/opinion/nigeria-negotiations-shehu-sani/index.html?iid=article_sidebar"><img src="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnn/dam/assets/130929203511-boko-haram-screengrab-abubakar-shekau-video-tease.jpg" alt="" border="0" height="68" width="120"/></a>
</div>
<div class="cnn_stryscbx4">Until the abduction of more than 200 girls from a school in rural Chibok, Nigeria's Boko Haram insurgency received scant attention in the global media.</div>
